        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_abyræg" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d3151e66" xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>abyræg</orth></form>
                <form xml:id="form_d3151e69" xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>abæreg</orth><form xml:id="form_d3151e71" type="variant"><orth>abæræg</orth></form></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3151e74"><sense xml:id="sense_d3151e75"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>абрек</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>%iabrek%i (Caucasian bandit)</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d3151e84"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>разбойник</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>outlaw</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3151e96">
                        <quote>æxæstony bæsty x˳yzdær særibar abyræg</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вместо тюрьмы лучше быть свободным абреком</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>it is better than prison to be a free outlaw</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>145</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3151e115">
                        <quote>ḱī abyræg alyǧdī, ḱī xæxty bambæxstī, qalon nal fystoj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кто убежал в абреки, кто спрятался в горах, податей больше не
                                платили</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>some became outlaws, some hid in the mountains, they never paid taxes
                                anymore</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>13</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3151e134">
                        <quote>īw læg… abyrǵytæm baftydī</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>некоторый человек… попался разбойникам</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>some person … came into the hands of outlaws</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Лука"/><biblScope>%i10%i
                            30</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3151e153" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>fættærgaj dæn næ adæmæj, abæregæj raliǧtæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>обиделся я на наш народ, убежал от него абреком</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I was offended at our people, I ran away from it as an outlaw</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Wadž."/><biblScope>26</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3151e175" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>fesqætæg æj ænæbari æ warzontæj, æ bæstæj; ku ne ‘ncadæj æ xæʒari,
                            abæreg nom in issæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он был оторван против воли от любимых, от родины; не знал он покоя в
                                своем доме, и стало ему имя — абрек</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he was separated from his loved ones, from his motherland against his
                                will; he didn't know peace at home, and he came to be called an
                                outlaw</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Sozur"/><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3151e198" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>abærgutæ æcægæj ærbaǧuztæncæ ærǧawmæ, fal sæ armi neci
                            baftudæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>абреки действительно подкрались к стаду, но им не удалось ничем
                                поживиться</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the outlaws did actually reach the herd, but they didn't manage to
                                take anything</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1949 II
                            38</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3151e220" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>kæd æbærgutæ an, wæddær digorænttæ xunnæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>хоть мы и абреки, все же мы называемся дигорцами</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>although we are outlaws, we are called Digor after all</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MD"/><biblScope>1940 III
                            60</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">„Кавказское“ слово, восходящее, возможно, к <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e245" xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>*āparak</w></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e250" xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>āpartan</w>
                        <gloss><q>добыча</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e258" xml:lang="pal"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>грабить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e264" xml:lang="pal"><w>āpar</w>
                        <gloss><q>грабеж</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e270" xml:lang="fa" extralang="tr"><lang/>
                        <w>āvāra</w>
                        <gloss><q>бродяга</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e279" xml:lang="fa" extralang="tr"><w>āvār</w>
                        <gloss><q>добыча</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e285" xml:lang="fa" extralang="tr"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>грабеж</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e291" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>avar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e296" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>avari</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e301" xml:lang="ka"><w>avara</w>
                        <gloss><q>бродяга</q></gloss></mentioned>; ближе к осетинскому стоят:
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e307" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>abrakʼi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e313" xml:lang="ka"><w>abragi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e316" xml:lang="ka"><w>apʼarekʼa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e319" xml:lang="xmf"><lang/>
                        <w>abragi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e324" xml:lang="sva"><lang/>
                        <w>ambreg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e329" xml:lang="ab"><lang/>
                        <w>abrag</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e334" xml:lang="abq"><lang/>
                        <w>abrag</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e340" xml:lang="kbd" extralang="kbd-x-crc"><lang/>
                        <w>abreg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e345" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>abrek</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e350" xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>äbarg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e355" xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>oburg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e360" xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>aburik</w></mentioned>.%r1%r Ср. также <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e365" xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>aparag</w>
                        <gloss><q>пришелец</q></gloss></mentioned>. Различие между формами типа
                    %iaparek(abareg)%i и %iavara%i следует объяснить тем, что первые усвоено в
                    южнорусские, особенно казачьи говоры, а также в русский литературный язык. Как
                    видно, персидское слово было усвоено в языки Кавказа дважды: сперва в
                    пехлевийской форме <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e374" xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>*āparak</w></mentioned> (отсюда <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e379" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>abrak-</w></mentioned> и пр.), потом в новоперсидской <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e384" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āvāra</w></mentioned> (отсюда <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e389" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>avara</w></mentioned> и пр.). Осетинское слово, как видно в особенности
                    из дигорской формы, усвоено от соседей; поэтому <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e394" xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>Ἄβραγος</w></mentioned> следует связать скорее с <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e399" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>abra-</w></mentioned>, ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arv"/>
                            ‘небо’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ВЯ"/><biblScope>1958 I
                            117—120</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">A “Caucasian” word that probably traces back to <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e415" xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>*āparak</w></mentioned>, cf. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e420" xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>āpartan</w>
                        <gloss><q>trophy</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e428" xml:lang="pal"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>rob</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e434" xml:lang="pal"><w>āpar</w>
                        <gloss><q>robbery</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e440" xml:lang="fa" extralang="tr"><lang/>
                        <w>āvāra</w>
                        <gloss><q>tramp</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e449" xml:lang="fa" extralang="tr"><w>āvār</w>
                        <gloss><q>trophy</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e455" xml:lang="fa" extralang="tr"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>robbery</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e461" xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>avar</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e466" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>avari</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e471" xml:lang="ka"><w>avara</w>
                        <gloss><q>tramp</q></gloss></mentioned>; the following words are closer to
                    Ossetic: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e477" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>abrakʼi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e483" xml:lang="ka"><w>abragi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e486" xml:lang="ka"><w>apʼarekʼa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e489" xml:lang="xmf"><lang/>
                        <w>abragi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e494" xml:lang="sva"><lang/>
                        <w>ambreg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e499" xml:lang="ab"><lang/>
                        <w>abrag</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e504" xml:lang="abq"><lang/>
                        <w>abrag</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e510" xml:lang="kbd" extralang="kbd-x-crc"><lang/>
                        <w>abreg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e515" xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>abrek</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e520" xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>äbarg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e525" xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>oburg</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e530" xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>aburik</w></mentioned>.%r1%r Cf. also <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e535" xml:lang="av"><lang/>
                        <w>aparag</w>
                        <gloss><q>newcomer</q></gloss></mentioned>. The difference between forms
                    like %iaparek (abareg)%i and %iavara%i should be explained by the fact that the
                    former were borrowed in the southern Russian dialects, especially Cossack
                    dialects, as well as in the Russian literary language. As it can be seen, the
                    Persian word was borrowed in the languages ​​of the Caucasus twice: first in the
                    Pahlavi form <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e544" xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>*āparak</w></mentioned> (from here <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e549" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>abrak-</w></mentioned> etc.), and then in New Persian <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e554" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āvāra</w></mentioned> (from here <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e559" xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>avara</w></mentioned> etc.). The Ossetic word, as it can be seen
                    especially from the Digor form, was learned from neighbors; so <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e564" xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>Ἄβραγος</w></mentioned> should be rather connected with <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3151e569" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>abra-</w></mentioned>, Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arv"/>
                            ‘sky’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ВЯ"/><biblScope>1958 I
                            117—120</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="ru" n="1">Ошибочно: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>62</biblScope></bibl> (от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byryn"/> ‘ползти’!).</note>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="en" n="1">The following is incorrect: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>62</biblScope></bibl> (from <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byryn"/> ‘crawl’!).</note>
